  "title": "CIVIL ENGINEERING CONSULTANT",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities.</strong></p>\n<p>· To review all Authority's and Contractor's drawings</p>\n<p>· To supervise all Civil, Structural and Geotechnical building works, both permanent and temporary</p>\n<p>· To review Contractor's design and submission and supervise all works associated with Civil and Structural works</p>\n<p>· To ensure that contractor had obtained all necessary permits (NOA, NOC, POWS, TM approval, PTD, PTW, etc) and clearance to work</p>\n<p>· To conduct site inspection and ensure that contractor(s) implement corrective actions and timely preventive/mitigation measures whenever necessary</p>\n<p>· To ensure proper coordination among Contractor, AC, QP(D), relevant agencies, including interfacing contractors and consultants etc. for the works</p>\n<p>· To review formwork structure, formwork support systems prior to concreting works and ensure the formworks erected are PE endorsed with Certificate of Supervision (COS) issued</p>\n<p>· To upkeep safety, environmental and health matters while working at a construction site</p>\n<p>· To supervise the installation/decommissioning of instrumentation</p>\n<p>· To review the monitoring data and ensure the Civil and Structural works do not have huge impact on surrounding structures</p>\n<p>· To ensure daily register of Request for Information (RIN) for the works and proper documentation are in-placed during the entire construction/reinstatement phase</p>\n<p>· To participate in routine audits by the Authority/Developer, join in all joint inspections and safety site walks</p>\n<p>· To prepare and submit daily/weekly/monthly reports as required by the Authority/Developer</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>· Qualified candidates please submit in your updated resume in MS Word format with your latest RTO cert attached.</p>\n<p>· Diploma or Degree in Civil and Structural Engineering.</p>\n<p>· At least 4 years’ of experience, of which 2 years’ experience in MRT Rail or Road works that includes supervision of temporary and permanent works.</p>\n<p>· Possess a valid RE/RTO cert 2025 by JAC of IES/ACES.</p>\n<p>· Possess BCSS and/or confined space certificate and/or working at height certificate.</p>\n<p>· Candidate to be able to work shift works due to the demands of the project</p>\n<p>· Willing to work 56hrs work week</p>\n<p>· Salary range quoted is all in. i.e. inclusive of leave and MC benefits and gratuity/13month</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
